  "texts": [
    "Related workTime series forecasting plays a vital role in numerous domains, including renewable energy, air quality management, demand forecasting, and weather prediction.",
    "Traditional statistical methods like ARIMA (Auto-regressive Integrated Moving Average) have remained widely used for their accuracy, efficiency, and ease of use [9].",
    "However, recent studies have shown that machine learning methods, including recurrent neural networks (RNN) and deep learning approaches like LSTM, are gaining traction in time series forecasting [15,16].",
    "These methods have demonstrated strong performance, particularly in situations involving larger sample sizes [15].",
    "In the field of renewable energy forecasting, deep learning models such as LSTM have been employed for short-term wind speed prediction, showing promising results when compared to traditional statistical models [17,18]."
  ],
